org.forgerock.openam.rest.query

Class DataQueryFilterVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.rest.query.DataQueryFilterVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.forgerock.util.query.QueryFilterVisitor<Set<String>,Map<String,Map<String,Set<String>>>,org.forgerock.json.JsonPointer>

    public class DataQueryFilterVisitor
extends Object
implements org.forgerock.util.query.QueryFilterVisitor<Set<String>,Map<String,Map<String,Set<String>>>,org.forgerock.json.JsonPointer>
    Raw data query filter visitor for resources. It will filter against data read from the data store, which has the following structure: Map<String, Map<String, Set<String>>>

    The outer map holds a resource ID as the key. The inner map (value of the outer map) holds the names of the attributes of the resource as keys and a set of values for that attribute as the value.

    Each visit will return a set of IDs of resources that satisfied the filter criteria.
    Since:
    13.0.0
